body:
Hi, I found that verilator incorrectly infers clock signals based on the block sensitivity list when generating libraries, which causes pure combinatorial logic libraries to have unintended behavior during simulation.

Attached is a circuit module generated by Bluespec with a sensitive list written not with * but with the use of the referenced signals.

```verilog
  always@(comb_decode_inst or
	  IF_comb_decode_inst_BITS_31_TO_26_2_EQ_0b0_3_T_ETC___d66)
  begin
    case (comb_decode_inst[14:12])
      3'b0: CASE_comb_decode_inst_BITS_14_TO_12_0b0_0_0b1__ETC__q1 = 4'd0;
      // ......
    endcase
  end
```

In the generated wrapper code you can see that these signals are identified as driving the timing circuit:
```systemverilog
    // Combinatorialy evaluate changes to inputs
    always @* begin
        last_combo_seqnum__V = controller_protectlib_combo_update(
            handle__V
            , comb_decode_combo__V
        );
    end
    
    // Evaluate clock edges
    always @(posedge comb_decode_inst or negedge comb_decode_inst) begin
        controller_protectlib_combo_ignore(
            handle__V
        );
        last_seq_seqnum__V <= controller_protectlib_seq_update(
            handle__V
            , comb_decode_inst
            , comb_decode_tmp__V
        );
        comb_decode_seq__V <= comb_decode_tmp__V;
    end
    
    // Select between combinatorial and sequential results
    always @* begin
        if (last_seq_seqnum__V > last_combo_seqnum__V) begin
            comb_decode = comb_decode_seq__V;
        end
        else begin
            comb_decode = comb_decode_combo__V;
        end
    end
```

This causes the output of the module to always be 0 during simulation.
If I change the sensitive list in the source code to *, the generated code will eliminate the incorrect sequential logic and simulate properly:

```systemverilog
    // Combinatorialy evaluate changes to inputs
    always @* begin
        last_combo_seqnum__V = controller_protectlib_combo_update(
            handle__V
            , comb_decode_inst
            , comb_decode_combo__V
        );
    end
    
    // Select between combinatorial and sequential results
    always @* begin
        comb_decode = comb_decode_combo__V;
    end
```

### Environment
- OS: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS
- Verilator: 5.010 2023-04-30

[module_comb_decode.v.txt](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/files/11584163/module_comb_decode.v.txt)
